Citation.sTitle: Isobaric Vapor Liquid Equilibrium Data of 2-Methyl-propan-2-ol (1) + Heptan-1-ol (2), Methanol (1) + Heptan-1-ol (2), Ethanol (1) + Heptan-1-ol (2), and Propan-1-ol (1) + Heptan-1-ol (2) at 96.5 kPa
Citation.sAbstract: Isobaric vapor liquid equilibrium data at a local atmospheric pressure of 96.5 kPa is reported for the four binary systems, namely, 2-methyl propan-2-ol (1) + heptan-1-ol (2), methanol (1) + heptan-1-ol (2), ethanol (1) + heptan-1-ol (2), and propan-1-ol (1) + heptan-1-ol (2). The experiments are done using a Swietoslawski-type ebulliometer. The liquid-phase activity coefficients are modeled using the well-established Wilson model and the universal functional (UNIFAC) group contribution method. The data are found to be thermodynamically consistent.
